sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K912033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct was developed by Northwestern's 2012 iGEM team as part of a phytase producing vector meant to self lyse in high chloride and low pH conditions. The device is designed to lyse in the presence of high chloride concentrations. The Pgad promoter in front of the lysis cassette is activated by the combination of high extracellular hydrogen ion concentration and the presence of high intracellular chloride ion concentration.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grant Nicholas
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lysis:registry CP/RBS: registry clc-ec1: PCR from genome Pgad: PCR from vector from CUHK 2011 team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: None besides designing primers properly

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112808
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Enterobacteria phage T4 Lysis Device - no promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the lysis device using three genes from enterobacteria phage T4: lysozyme, holin, and antiholin. Various promoters can be installed with this device to control the lysis of bacteria. Antiholin has its own constitutive promoter to prevent the formation of holin multimers from basal expression. When the device is off, higher expression of antiholin compared to holin is required for better stability of the device.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pubmed Accession Number: NC_000866 Enterobacteria phage T4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: [Pcon].[Antiholin].[terminator] was assembled first, and then assembled with [T4 holin].[terminator]; Constitutive expression of antiholin is required before assembling holin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K912012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct was developed by Northwestern's 2012 iGEM team as part of a phytase producing vector meant to self lyse in high chloride and low pH conditions. The device is designed to constitutively produce CLC-EC1, a chloride-hydrogen antiporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grant Nicholas
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: CLC-EC1: PCR'd out from genome Constitutive promoter: parts registry RBS: parts registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No additional design considerations besides making primers

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pgad
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Pgad is chloride-sensitive promoter which was first discovered in Lactococcus lactis1, which is a gram-positive bacterium which can live in acidic environment. In this operon, gadC is glutamate-gamma-aminobutyrate antiporter and gadB is glutamate decarboxylase. They are both involved in intracellular pH regulation and co-expressed in the same operon under the control of Pgad2. The gene before Pgad, named gadR, which is constitutively expressed under the control of PgadR, is a positive regulator of Pgad coupled genes while intracellular chloride is level elevated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jacky, Fong Chuen, Loo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The gene sequence was obtained from the cassette from bp 821 to 2071 of GenBank sequence AF005098, which includes PgadR, gadR, Pgad and the starting codon ATG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Synthesized part by GenScript,all the illegal sites for RFC 10 (EcoRI, XbaI, SpeI, PstI) have been substituted by other codon producing the same amino acid in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Holins from T4 bacteriophage assemble together to form pores on inner membrane of bacteria allowing lysozyme to reach periplasm and degrade peptidoglycan layer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Making composite part of rbs.holin is problematic unless antiholin is expressed in bacteria together. Antiholin binds holin and inhibits the formation of holin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112806
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The lysozyme from enterobacteria phage T4 degrades peptidoglycan layer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jin Huh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: High expression of lysozyme only is toxic to bacteria.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
